  "texts": [
    "We are currently collaborating with clinicians in the SERENADE project 5, collecting data from the smart homes of a significantly large group of subjects, mostly living alone and diagnosed with Mild Cognitive Impairment.",
    "Our long-term objective in this project is a fine-grained recognition of the onset of cognitive decline.",
    "The sensor data that we are collecting in these homes is unlabeled, and we plan to adopt zeroshot ADL-LLM to capture the performed ADLs in this setting and work from there on detecting behavioral changes and anomalies under the guidance of clinicians.",
    "Appendix: LargeLanguage Models are Zero-Shot Recognizers for Activities of Daily Living GABRIELE CIVITARESE, MICHELE FIORI, PRIYANKAR CHOUDHARY, and CLAUDIO BETTINI, EveryWare Lab, Dept.",
    "of Computer Science, University of Milan, ItalyA Detailed results at different data availability scenarios In the following, we report the results of few-shot prompting (and the baselines) at different data availability scenarios: 100%, 50%, 25%, 10% of the training set."
  ],
